video.title: Brickleberry
video.synopsis: A second-tier national park and its mediocre ranger staff are forced to take their act up a notch to survive in this animated comedy for grown-ups.

episodes.synopsis: While Malloy cheats on his anti-junk food diet, Steve undermines new ranger Ethel to protect his monopoly on the Ranger of the Month award.
episodes.title: Welcome to Brickleberry

episodes.synopsis: Steve contracts a strange but deadly sexually transmitted disease from a prostitute, and Malloy wants to get revenge on a couple of raccoons.
episodes.title: 2 Weeks Notice

episodes.synopsis: Ethel tries to help Connie kick her psychic addiction. Steve and Denzel go undercover and get tangled up with pot-growing Russian mobsters.
episodes.title: Saved By the Balls

episodes.synopsis: When Woody sets his sights on showing up Yellowstone's cute animals, Steve proposes breeding a "squabbit" -- a squirrel-rabbit hybrid.
episodes.title: Squabbits

episodes.synopsis: A forest fire turns Denzel's skin white and Steve's skin black. Connie panics when her old Marine drill sergeant visits the park.
episodes.title: Race Off!

episodes.synopsis: Making scarce when an obnoxious anti-gay church holds a meeting in the park, Connie stumbles upon a secret missile base inside Brickleberry Mountain.
episodes.title: Gay Bomb

episodes.synopsis: When the crew gripes about working conditions, Woody replaces them with rangers from overseas. The gang bounces back by finding work in a strip club.
episodes.title: Hello Dottie

episodes.synopsis: When the rangers find out Steve wears a toupee, he drinks a potent hair tonic that works so well he's mistaken for Bigfoot.
episodes.title: Steve's Bald?

episodes.synopsis: With animal mutilations on the rise inside the park, Steve tracks the culprit and discovers his own father, a legendary ranger, living in a cave.
episodes.title: Daddy Issues

episodes.synopsis: The park floods after fireworks destroy the Brickleberry River dam, stranding the rangers and other survivors on top of Brickleberry Mountain.
episodes.title: The Dam Show

episodes.synopsis: When he discovers that the lake has healing powers, Woody cashes in by becoming a crackpot healer. Meanwhile, Denzel finds a frozen Neanderthal.
episodes.title: Miracle Lake

episodes.synopsis: Malloy becomes a film director to help Woody resurrect his career as a porn star, and Steve blames his problems on the Brickleberry Ghost.
episodes.title: The Comeback

episodes.synopsis: Woody takes up yoga and joins his teacher's outlandish cult. Ethel takes charge of the park, and Denzel spends an inheritance on a jet pack.
episodes.title: Woody's Girl

episodes.synopsis: When Bobby discovers that he's the rightful owner of the park's land, he evicts the rangers and transforms Brickleberry into a trailer park.
episodes.title: Brickleberry Trailer Park

episodes.synopsis: The members of a traveling carnival sideshow captivate Connie, and Malloy helps Steve sue the park after he gets paralyzed on the job.
episodes.title: Crippleberry

episodes.synopsis: Preparing to compete in the annual Ranger Games, Denzel learns to ice skate, Steve takes steroids, and Woody unwittingly recruits a terrorist.
episodes.title: Ranger Games

episodes.synopsis: When the irate governor puts a highway through the park, Woody and Ethel each decide to run for office. Meanwhile, Connie joins Bobby's militia.
episodes.title: My Way or the Highway

episodes.synopsis: Desperate to impress her big sister, Ethel convinces Connie to pose as her husband and shaves off Malloy's fur to pass him off as her son.
episodes.title: Little Boy Malloy

episodes.synopsis: A moose talks Malloy into leading an animal insurrection by revealing that humans killed his parents, but Steve tries to suppress the truth.
episodes.title: The Animals Strike Back

episodes.synopsis: Denzel calls in some fellas from Detroit to scare Malloy straight, but they all end up behind bars, where Malloy starts running a gang.
episodes.title: Scared Straight

episodes.synopsis: Brickleberry is selected to play a role in a mission to Mars. But when the rangers discover that the space program is a hoax, they are taken prisoner.
episodes.title: Trip to Mars

episodes.synopsis: Flamey the Bear comes to Brickleberry to promote the park's reopening, but instead he gets drunk and goes on a destructive rampage.
episodes.title: My Favorite Bear

episodes.synopsis: Connie gives birth to a baby who might be the Antichrist. While Woody and Malloy seek refuge in a bunker, Steve and the others plot to kill the child.
episodes.title: A-Park-a-Lypse

episodes.synopsis: A visit from President Obama coincides with a risky surgical procedure involving Woody, Steve and a shared liver.
episodes.title: Obamascare

episodes.synopsis: A snooty country club that welcomes Denzel wants nothing to do with Woody. Malloy fights for the right to express himself.
episodes.title: In Da Club

episodes.synopsis: While Connie and Ethel go head-to-head in a beauty contest, Denzel and Steve decide to join forces in the bedroom.
episodes.title: Miss National Park

episodes.synopsis: While Connie obsesses over "Wheel of Fortune" host Pat Sajak, Woody and Denzel work through their awkward new family dynamic.
episodes.title: That Brother's My Father

episodes.synopsis: With Denzel's help, Steve launches an unlikely career as a gay icon. Meanwhile, Malloy gets his wish to be "big."
episodes.title: Write 'em Cowboy

episodes.synopsis: After a visit from the secretary of the interior leads to Woody's demotion, Denzel decides to clean up his act.
episodes.title: Old Wounds

episodes.synopsis: Ethel contemplates her future when a pregnancy test turns up positive. The other rangers take up residence in a mental ward.
episodes.title: Baby Daddy

episodes.synopsis: Connie and Denzel get stranded on an island, but it's far from deserted. Steve believes himself to be a pirate after a hypnosis gone horribly wrong.
episodes.title: Steve the Fearless Pilot

episodes.synopsis: Woody loses the park in a poker bet, and Steve struggles with his rapid expansion. Malloy must mate with an ugly bear ... or else.
episodes.title: High Stakes

episodes.synopsis: Ethel's forced to look within when Woody hires a hot new ranger. A shocking discovery prompts Steve to question his résumé.
episodes.title: Amber Alert

episodes.synopsis: Woody's hemorrhoid problem proves oddly inspiring and attracts a global audience. Steve achieves his lifelong dream of becoming a police officer.
episodes.title: Cops and Bottoms

episodes.synopsis: Woody's decision to turn Brickleberry into a summer camp stirs up competition among the rangers over the promise of a "tribal shield."
episodes.title: Campin' Ain't Easy

episodes.synopsis: In the series finale, Woody tries to thwart a newly Amish Ethel's attempts to go green while Malloy confronts his fear of cows.
episodes.title: Global Warning
